Hi @rnesolydev!

I think you're just missing this css:

```css
/* rows hidden by filtering */
.tablesorter .filtered {
	display: none;
}
```

The class name is set by the [`filter_filteredRow` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#widget-filter-filteredrow).

There is no way to customize the output right now, unless you were to override the blueprint.

With that said:

1) I am working actively on a new release that will include this feature;
2) You could just add an [exception handler](http://sanic.readthedocs.io/en/latest/sanic/exceptions.html#handling-exceptions)

```python
@app.exception(exceptions.AuthenticationFailed)
def exception_response(request, exception):
    return response.text(str(exception), status=exception.status_code)
```

