Regarding `Instance.castable`, if it supported also a `cast(obj, trait, value)` callable into the constructor args, it would only need few lines to support auto-populating containers with nested `Configurables`:
```python
class C(Configurable):
    i = CInt(config=True)

def cast_config(obj, trait, config_dict):
    trait.klass(parent=obj, **config_dict)

class A(Configurable):
    a = List(Instance(C, 
                      castable=dict, 
                      cast=cast_config, 
                      config=True), 
             config=True)

cfg = ({
    'A': {
        'a': [
            {}, 
            {'i': 1}, 
            {}
        ], 
        'C': {'i': -2}  # default for empty elements in the list.
    }}
a = A(config=Config(cfg))
assert [e.i for e in a.a] == [-2, 1, -2]
```
