@hamishwillee, without this functionality, DKPY2 is, in some respects, a retrograde step compared to DK1. There are a number of use cases for for the forwarding that don't utilise *any* of the other functionality of MAVProxy, so you're loading up your companion (or other) computer for nothing if you have to run both DKPY2 and MAVProxy.

1) My case - lightweight ground indicator with forwarding to tablet / PC. The only functionality being useed from MAVProxy is the forwarding, but MAVproxy (AFAIK) doesn't handle connection failures well - a USB-based reconnect that increments your ttyUSBx will not recover, and you can't build in any smart logic for detecting baud rate mismatches. All those things are feasible with DKPY2 ... except for the forwarding.

2) Wifi / cellular / other telemetry - if you want to pass your data over anything other than a serial port connection from the on-board autopilot, you need to run it through a companion computer. This requires the whole of MAVProxy just to pass it from a serial input on the Pi to a USB or network interface. If you want to concurrently use and DK functionality, you have to do the output doubling from MAVProxy.

